text.tspan: Assurance and Joy of Salvation — General
To fulfill all the law, He took my place;
He obeyed, e’en suffering, my sin to erase.
Jesus has satisfied God’s heart, and set me free!
Now I open my heart, to offer praise to Thee.
For all You’ve done for me.
Wondrous news You’ve revealed—now I can see!
Oh, what grace! Your love divine is flowing in me!
Eyes full of tenderness! Beholding face to face,
Now I open my heart, to offer praise to Thee.
For all You’ve shown to me.
Riven veil—living way thus He affords.
He arose, the work completed! Oh, praise the Lord!
Now I can boldly come into the holiest place!
Now I open my heart, to offer praise to Thee.
